name: sulfate-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + sulfateout = ADP + phosphate + sulfatein [RN:R00086]
comment: ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. A bacterial enzyme that imports sulfate and thiosulfate anions.

references.title: Sulfate and thiosulfate transport in Escherichia coli K-12: evidence for a functional overlapping of sulfate- and thiosulfate-binding proteins.
Phylogenetic analyses of the ATP-binding constituents of bacterial extracytoplasmic receptor-dependent ABC-type nutrient uptake permeases.
Molecular phylogeny as a basis for the classification of transport proteins from bacteria, archaea and eukarya.
